quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  4,66,"And if We had prescribed for them that they should kill themselves or that they should migrate from their homeland, they would have not done it, except a few of them. And if they had done what they were advised to do it would have been better for them, and more effective in making (them) firm."
  4,67,"And in that case, We would have certainly given them a great reward"
  4,68,"and we would have certainly led them to a straight path."
  4,69,"And those who obey Allah and the Messenger are with those whom Allah has blessed, namely, the prophets, the Siddiqin1, the Shuhada'2, and the righteous - and what a good company they are."
  4,70,"That grace is from Allah and Allah is sufficient being the One who knows."
  4,71,"0 those who believe, take your precautions and march in groups or march off all together."
  4,72,"And among you there is one who shall invariably fall back; then, if some calamity befalls you, he would say, "Allah has been so generous to me since I was not present with them.""
  4,73,"And if there comes to you some bounty from Allah, he shall be saying - as if there was no friendship between you and him - "0 that I would have been with them, then, I would have achieved a great success.""
  4,74,"So, those who sell the worldly life for the Hereafter should fight in the way of Allah. And whoever fights in the way of Allah then gets killed or prevails, to him We shall give a great reward."